# Librora frontend — environment variables

# Base URL of the backend API. Defaults to http://localhost:3001 if unset.
# VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3001

# Library Clipper extension ID — used to detect the extension and hand off the
# logged-in session via chrome.runtime.sendMessage. Find the ID at
# chrome://extensions (dev, with Developer mode on) or the Chrome Web Store
# listing once published. Leave unset to disable extension detection entirely.
# VITE_EXTENSION_ID=

# Cloudflare Turnstile site key (public, safe to expose in the client bundle —
# it identifies the site, not a secret). Get from: Cloudflare Dashboard →
# Turnstile. Leave unset and the register page skips rendering the widget;
# the backend's TurnstileService then also skips verification if its own
# TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY is unset, so local dev works with neither configured.
# VITE_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY=
